"No, it wouldn't!" he almost snapped, surprising her. "You sounded like somebody else for a moment there. It doesn't become you to behave like a -- a tart, Di."
"Nigel—!" she gasped. "I didn't mean to behave like anything of the kind. I was only joking." "Well, don't. It's miserable enough my having to take my leave in the autumn without you trying to be bright and gay about it.
